Column Comment.0: GEODETIC DATUM IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for the geodetic datum.
Column Comment.1: ACTIVE INDICATOR: A Y/N flag indicating whether this row of data is currently eitheractive / valid (Y) or inactive / invalid (N).
Column Comment.2: DATUM ORIGIN: Entries in this column identify the valid origins for GeodeticDatums. For example, Geocentric, Local Origin, Local Meridian.
Column Comment.3: EFFECTIVE DATE: The date that the data in this row first came into effect.
Column Comment.4: ELLIPSOID IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for the ellipsoids of revolution.
Column Comment.5: EXPIRY DATE: The date that the data in this row was no longer active or in effect.
Column Comment.6: GEODETIC DATUM AREA: The area over which the Geodetic Datum is valid.
Column Comment.7: GEODETIC DATUM AREA TYPE: The type of area over which the datum is valid,such as country or continent.
Column Comment.8: GEODETIC DATUM NAME: Common name given to the geodetic datum.
Column Comment.9: ORIGIN ANGULAR OUOM: The original UOM for the latitude, longitude values of thegeodetic datum origin.
Column Comment.10: ORIGIN LATITUDE: The latitude of the point of origin for a local datum or localmeridian. This is a historical artifact and is scheduled to be dropped in PPDM 3.8.
Column Comment.11: ORIGIN LONGITUDE: The longitude of the point of origin for a local datum or localmeridian. This is a historical artifact and is scheduled to be dropped in PPDM 3.8.
Column Comment.12: DATUM ORIGIN NAME: Name given to the point of origin for a local datum or localmeridian. This is a historical artifact and is scheduled to be dropped in PPDM 3.8.
Column Comment.13: ROW_MANAGEMENT_GUID: This value may be used to provide a global uniqueidentifier for this row of data. Use of this column is not mandatory, but if used,optional PPDM NOT NULL and UNIQUE INDEX constraints provided in the datamodel DDL should be created.
Column Comment.14: REMARK: Narrative remarks about this row of data.
Column Comment.15: SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as thesource of information for this row.
Column Comment.16: DOCUMENT SOURCE: A list of document types that are used as the source forsupplying data. For example government and regulatory forms, oper ator reports orscout tickets.
Column Comment.17: ROW CHANGED BY: Application login id of the user who last changed the row.
Column Comment.18: ROW CHANGED DATE: System date of the last time the row was changed.
Column Comment.19: ROW CREATED BY: System user who created this row of data.
Column Comment.20: ROW CREATED DATE: Date that the row was created on.
Column Comment.21: ROW_EFFECTIVE_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of datais effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row of data wasmade available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.22: ROW_EXPIRY_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of data isno longer effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row ofdata was no longer available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.23: PPDM ROW QUALITY: A set of values indicating the quality of data in this row,usually with reference to the method or procedures used to load the data, althoughother types of quality reference are permitted.
